# Button Component Rule

The [Button.vue](mdc:src/components/ui/Button/Button.vue) component follows shadcn-vue conventions:

- Single File Component (SFC) in `src/components/ui/Button`.
- Provides a flexible button with variants (`primary`, `secondary`, `tertiary`, `ghost`, `link`) and sizes (`default`, `sm`, `lg`, `icon`).
- Uses [class-variance-authority](mdc:https:/cva.style/docs/integrations/vue) for variant management.
- Accepts `as`, `variant`, `size`, `active`, and `activeClassname` props.
- Uses Tailwind CSS for styling and utility classes.
- Renders as a configurable HTML element via the `as` prop (default: `button`).
- Follows accessibility and shadcn-vue best practices for button components.

For usage and API, see the [shadcn-vue Button documentation](mdc:https:/www.shadcn-vue.com/docs/components/button).




